  "text": "These findings indicate that whilst UK-born students express a clear preference for native varieties of English spoken in the country, when the informants' ratings of the L1 and the L2 English speech forms included in the study were considered independently, the inconsistencies found point to the different attitude components of status and social attractiveness to be highly complex and in opposition. Hence, given the complexity and contradictory nature of UKborn students implicit attitudes towards linguistic diversity in both native and non-native spoken English, it is possible to infer that the participants, listening to and evaluating the recordings, are reacting emotionally as well as cognitively to each of the speech samples, and that these affective and cognitive components are particularly contradictory when the most fine-grained judgements are required (see [CITATION_1] ), i.e., beyond simple comparisons between L1 and L2 English speech.",
